                      <persName>ܫܦܝܪܐ</persName>
                    </quote>), and was born about<date>A. Gr. 732</date>,<date>A.D. 421</date>
                    <!-- How do I mark up? -->. A voice from heaven announced that at the age of two years he would confute the heathen kings and destroy their idols:<quote xml:lang="syr">ܫܒܪܐ ܕܡܬܝ̣ܠܕ ܠܟܘܢ ܟܕ ܢܗܘܐ ܒܪ ܬܪ̈ܬܝܢ ܫ̈ܢܝܢ܆ ܢ݁ܰܟ̣ܣ ܠܡ̈ܠܟܐ ܥܲܘ̈ܠܐ ܘܢܣ̣ܚܘܦ ܠܦܬܟܪ̈ܝܗܘܢ̣ ܘܢܬܩ̣ܪܐ ܫܡܗ ܛܠܝܐ.<locus facs="426b" to="426b"/>
                    </quote>This rumour spreading abroad, the child was brought before<persName>Alexander, the governor of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/52">Byblos or Jubail</placeName>
                    </persName>(<quote>
                      <placeName ref=" http://syriaca.org/place/52">ܓܷܒܠܷܝܗ̇ ܡܕܝܢܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܣܦ̇ܪ ܝ̇ܰܡ̣ܐ</placeName>
                    </quote>), who put both him and his parents to death.</note>
